<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n54117c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n54" href="#n54117c">N54 (VI.B.45)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n54all.htm#n54117c"> 117(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Colderna ~</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">On each boss is placed a star of night; Can-mathon with beams unshorn; <mark>Col-derna</mark>, rising from a cloud; Uloicho robed in mist; and the soft beam of Cathlin glittering on a rock. Smiling, on its own blue wave, Reldurath half-sinks its western light. The red eye of Berthin looks, through a grove, on the hunter &hellip; Wide, in the midst, arose the cloudless beams of Tonth&eacute;na, that star which looked by night on the course of the sea-tossed Larthon: Larthon ,the first of Bolga&apos;s race, who travelled on the wind. <br>281n: Col-derna, <i>slant and sharp beam</i>. <small> James MacPherson, <a name="JMPO2" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#JMPO2"><cite title="source">The Poems of Ossian</cite></a> (1806), Vol. II, <font size="-1">TEMORA</font> Book VII, 281</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
